Stock Configuration & Condition: This rifle has an aluminum receiver that takes the place of a stock, but there is a pistol grip and a recoil pad on the back of the receiver. The recoil pad is a thick black solid rubber pad. It shows a few light marks. The pistol grip is black synthetic with checkering on its sides and serrations on the backstrap. There is a prominent finger rest on the front strap for the middle finger of the shooting hand. The grip shows no handling marks and the checkering shows extremely light wear. The LOP measures 14 ¼” from the front of the trigger to the back of the recoil pad. The recoil pad and grip are in about Excellent condition. Type of Finish: The barrel has a matte black parkerized finish and the receiver has a matte black anodized finish.  Bore Condition: The bore is bright with sharp rifling. There is no erosion. Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 99% of its metal finish. There are a few light marks scattered over the top of the muzzle brake, on the barrel and the bolt handle, with a scratch through the finish on the underside of the barrel. There is a light mark on the lower shoulders of each side of the receiver where the bipod can rub and a light mark on the left side of the receiver at the front of the safety. The screw heads are Allen heads. The markings are clear. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition. Mechanics: The action functions correctly. There is a large fan shaped muzzle brake screwed and clamped to the front of the barrel. We have not fired this rifle. Box, Paperwork & Accessories: This rifle comes with a factory bipod mounted on the underside of the front section of the receiver. It is detachable, and the legs fold as well as adjust for length. There are also separate, removable sections of the foam in the lid and the bottom of the case for storage of accessories. Please see our pictures for more detail. The lid of the case has a label marked “PELICAN / 1750 CASE” and the front face of the bottom section has a white label marked with the make, model and serial number of this rifle. The case has a large synthetic handle with four clasps securing the lid. There are multiple light handling marks on the outside of the case. The foam on the inside of the case appears undamaged. Well, this is certainly a rifle. From Barrett’s website: “Rugged. Reliable. Uncomplicated. The Model 99 is designed for one thing only: to get the job done. With its brilliantly simple design, hard-core construction and surprisingly few moving parts, it offers match-winning accuracy time and time again. Available in both .50 BMG and .416 Barrett, the Model 99 brings new levels of long-range precision shooting. Known as much for its dependability as its versatility, the Model 99 has unfailing accuracy you can rely on.”. This is a Barrett Model 99 rifle with a 32” barrel chambered in .416 Barrett. It has a 3 port fan shaped muzzle brake, M1913 steel Picatinny optics rail, a detachable bipod with adjustable legs, a match grade trigger and a bolt with enough threads on it to lock-up Fort Knox. It comes with a 10X Bushnell Elite 3200 scope and its Pelican hard case.
